Production testing identified several product-level improvements.

Atlas currently:

✓ Successfully coordinates executive departments.

✓ Maintains persistent institutional knowledge.

✓ Produces structured deliverables.

✓ Tracks autonomous execution.

✓ Preserves truthful execution boundaries.

However, founder testing also revealed opportunities to improve the
experience.

Future development should:

• Reduce repetitive messaging.

• Eliminate duplicated executive summaries.

• Replace technical implementation language with executive language.

• Hide internal execution mechanics.

• Surface completed work instead of implementation state.

• Continue work automatically whenever possible.

• Interrupt the founder only when human authority is genuinely required.

These findings become official product requirements for all future
milestones.

