====================================================================
CURRENT DEVELOPMENT PRIORITIES
====================================================================

Priority 1

AT-018 — Founder Experience Simplification

Purpose

Transform Atlas into a founder-first operating system by reducing
complexity, eliminating repetitive communication, hiding implementation
details, and surfacing only meaningful business outcomes.

Primary Objectives

• Simplify every founder-facing page.

• Remove duplicated executive messaging.

• Replace implementation language with executive language.

• Reduce dashboard content to essential decisions.

• Introduce progressive disclosure throughout Atlas.

• Make Atlas feel like an experienced CEO rather than software.

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 2

AT-019 — Autonomous Authority Model

Purpose

Allow Atlas to execute every action within its authority automatically.

Atlas should interrupt the founder only when:

• Money must be spent.

• A legal commitment is required.

• An irreversible external business action is required.

Everything else proceeds automatically.

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 3

AT-020 — Patent Intelligence & External Research

Purpose

Connect Atlas to live patent intelligence providers and create
source-grounded novelty, prior-art, claim comparison, and design-around
analysis.

Primary Objectives

• Live patent search

• Claim comparison

• Novelty scoring

• Prior-art analysis

• Design-around recommendations

• Continuous patent monitoring

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 4

AT-021 — Validation Automation

Purpose

Allow Atlas to automatically publish, monitor, and analyze validation
activities through supported external providers.

Examples

• Landing pages

• Surveys

• Waitlists

• Analytics

• Validation reporting

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 5

AT-022 — Native CAD Generation

Purpose

Extend the existing CAD Foundation into full native geometry generation,
editing, visualization, STEP export, STL export, and engineering-ready
design outputs.

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 6

AT-023 — Commercialization Platform

Purpose

Expand Atlas into a complete commercialization platform capable of
coordinating manufacturing, licensing, retail, fundraising, pricing,
launch planning, and investor readiness.

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 7

Platform Expansion

Future development will continue adding executive capabilities,
external integrations, automation, and specialized intelligence while
preserving the existing Atlas Operating System architecture.

